<h2>7.5 - How do I switch consoles? <i>(i386)</i></h2>
d146 3
a148 1
On the i386, OpenBSD provides six virtual terminals by default,
d247 2
a248 1
which is used by X as a graphical screen.
d388 2
a389 2
<li>The two serial ports on a SPARC are labeled <i>ttya</i> and
<i>ttyb</i>.
@


1.50
log
@
Improvements in wording and content
from Tom Cosgrove (tom dot cosgrove at arches-consulting dot com)
